===Etymology===
From Hindustani [[हिन्दुस्तानी]] / {{URchar|[[ہندوستانی]]}} (hindustānī) < Persian {{FAchar|[[هند]]}} ('''hend''' = Hindu) + Persian {{FAchar|[[ستان]]}} ('''stān''' = ''land'') + adjective suffix {{FAchar|[[ی]]}} ('''ī''') resulting in ('''hendustānī''' = ''land of the Hindus'') < '''hend''' is derived from Sanskrit [[सिन्धु]] ('''sindhu'''), Sanskrit name for the [[Indus River]].

===Adjective===
'''Hindustani'''
# Related to [[India]], or historically the entire Indian [[subcontinent]].
